EBOLA UPDATE (40): COTE D'IVOIRE ex GUINEA, WHO, DETAILS
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 20 Aug 2021
Source: Bloomberg [edited]
https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-08-20/ebola-case-in-ivory-coast-spurs-urgent-hunt-for-source-in-guinea?sref=aOs3djJY


Disease trackers have yet to identify how a teenager from rural Guinea, treated for Ebola in a hospital in Abidjan, sparked Cote d'Ivoire's 1st outbreak of the deadly viral disease in 27 years.

The World Health Organization has sent expert teams to both West African nations to help authorities scale up measures to find and prevent additional cases, the agency's regional office in Brazzaville said in a statement Thursday [19 Aug 2021]. As of 18 Aug [2021], there was one confirmed and 3 suspected cases in Cote d'Ivoire that later tested negative, WHO said. The 6 high-risk contacts have been quarantined and 131 contacts identified. No deaths have been reported.

The 18-year-old patient traveled from the Labe region in Guinea, near the border with Senegal, to Abidjan, on public transport. She stopped multiple times during her 5-day trip, including through Nzerekore, Guinea's second-largest city, where an Ebola outbreak was declared over 2 months ago.

The teen developed a fever after leaving her home in rural Guinea. Her symptoms worsened to include headache and bleeding from her gums by the time she arrived in Abidjan, a city of almost 5 million people, on 12 Aug [2021], the WHO said in a report.

Some 5000 doses of Ebola vaccine are being administered to health-care workers, 1st responders, contacts and others at high risk of infection, the WHO said.

The authorities identified 33 contact cases in Cote d'Ivoire, including 6 passengers who were on the bus with the patient, the nation's Health Ministry said in a statement Friday [20 Aug 2021]. There were 3 of the passengers traced to the port city of San Pedro and the other 3 to the town of Duekoue, both in the heart of the country's cocoa-producing region.

As of Wednesday [18 Aug 2021], 49 people in contact with the Ebola patient have been identified in Guinea, and health authorities are preparing to vaccinate high-risk contacts there, the agency said.

[Byline: Jason Gale]

