Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[The number of confirmed cases remains at one but the number of suspected cases has increased to 3 with 6 high risk contacts identified and quarantined. There is still no indication about the subtype of Ebola virus that is involved in this confirmed case nor where she might have acquired the infection. Of the 6 ebolavirus subtypes, 3 -- _Zaire_, _Sudan_, _Bundibugyo_ -- have been associated with large ebolavirus disease outbreaks in Africa. One hopes that the virus subtype will be determined soon. - Mod.TY

